About


  
  
    
      Who am I?
      
        Hi, I'm Robert Gulmann, a final-year Business & Data Analytics student with a strong passion for finance, machine learning, and entrepreneurship. 
        I've worked in data analytics at EY and have experience in investment banking applications. I enjoy solving complex problems, developing innovative 
        business ideas, and staying ahead in the finance & tech space.
      
      
        In my free time, you'll find me training at the gym, traveling, or working on new projects. 
        I‚Äôm currently focused on machine learning and financial markets, aiming to bridge the gap between data science and investment strategy.
      
    
    
      
    
  

  
  
    
      What is this website about?
      
        This website serves as my personal ePortfolio, showcasing my skills, projects, and insights across 
        data analytics, finance, and technology. 
        Here, you‚Äôll find my work, blog posts, and recommendations that reflect my interests and professional journey.
      
    
    
      
    
  

  
  
    
      Why did I create this website?
      
        I wanted a space to document my journey, explore ideas, and create an online presence that reflects my passion for 
        technology, finance, and innovation. 
        This portfolio is a way to connect with like-minded individuals, share insights, and continuously improve my craft.
